{{Infobox book | <!-- See [[Wikipedia:WikiProject Novels]] or [[Wikipedia:WikiProject Books]] --> | name = Le Petit Robert De La Langue Française | title_orig = Le Petit Robert | translator = | author = [[Paul Robert (lexicographer)|Paul Robert]]; Josette Rey-Debove; [[Alain Rey]] | illustrator = | cover_artist = | country = France | language = [[French language|French]] | series = | genre = [[Reference]] | publisher = [[Dictionnaires Le Robert]] | release_date = 1967 | english_release_date = 2000 | media_type = | pages = 2841 | isbn = 2-85036-668-4 | oclc= 45079389 | preceded_by = | followed_by = }}
'''''Le Petit Robert''''' is a popular single-volume [[French language|French]] [[dictionary]] first published by [[Paul Robert (lexicographer)|Paul Robert]] in 1967, an abridgement of his eight-volume ''[[Dictionnaire alphabétique et analogique de la langue française]]''.<ref>{{cite web |title = Alain Rey: The Father of the Petit Robert |last = Kauffmann |first = Alexandre |publisher = France Magazine |date = Winter 2007–2008 |url = http://www.francemagazine.org/articles/issue84/article200.asp?issue_id=84&article_id=200 }}</ref>
{{As of|2008}}, it is in its fourth edition and is available in both print and electronic forms. It is also widely used across European nations. It is published by [[Dictionnaires Le Robert]].
